To connect a local repository with a remote repository.

Usage:

# Add remote repository
$ git remote <command> <remote_name> <remote_URL>

# List named remote repositories
$ git remote -v

In Practice:

# Adding a remote repository with the name of beans
$ git remote add origin git@account_name.git.beans.com:/account_name/repository_name.git

# list named remote repositories
$ git remote -v
origin git@account_name.git.beansapp.com:/account_name/repository_name.git (fetch)
origin git@account_name.git.beansapp.com:/account_name/repository_name.git (push)
